  <prompt>
    Update `SearchIndexNameResolver` to read the index name via FetchXml `link-entity` (outer join) from the `sprk_aisearchindexid` lookup expansion. Each step in the 3-step chain (document â†’ parent â†’ BU) uses a single fetch with a linked-entity attribute projection of `sprk_aisearchindex.sprk_searchindexname`. Retain the text-column read path as a fallback (for backward compatibility during migration soak); both paths log distinct messages so App Insights can confirm the migration. Replace the static `AiSearchOptions.AllowedIndexes` validation in `KnowledgeDeploymentService` with a new `DataverseAllowedIndexesProvider` that queries `sprk_aisearchindex` (statecode = 0, project `sprk_searchindexname`) with a 5-minute `IMemoryCache` TTL. Existing appsettings `AllowedIndexes` validation is retained as a final fallback (logged as warning when used).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    BFF developer with deep familiarity with `Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/`, `Spaarke.Dataverse`, FetchXml, and `IMemoryCache`. Read `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` before designing â€” binding pre-merge checklist.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SearchIndexNameResolver.ResolveAsync` reads from `sprk_aisearchindexid` lookup via FetchXml `link-entity` (outer); falls back to `sprk_searchindexname` text column when lookup is null (logged as "text-fallback"). `KnowledgeDeploymentService.GetSearchClientAsync` validates against `DataverseAllowedIndexesProvider.IsAllowedAsync` (cached query of `sprk_aisearchindex` rows where statecode = 0); on a Dataverse fetch failure, falls back to the appsettings `AllowedIndexes` array with a warning log. Existing BFF test suite passes unmodified (NFR-02-equivalent for Phase G).
  </goal>

