  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read existing `SearchIndexNameResolver.cs` (already loaded earlier in session). Map the 3-step chain (doc â†’ parent â†’ BU) and where each step calls `_entityService.RetrieveAsync`.</step>
    <step order="2">For each step, replace `RetrieveAsync(entityName, id, ["sprk_searchindexname", ...])` with a `RetrieveMultipleAsync(new FetchExpression(...))` using FetchXml with `link-entity` to `sprk_aisearchindex`, projecting `idx.sprk_searchindexname` as an `AliasedValue`. See spec Â§7 for the canonical FetchXml shape.</step>
    <step order="3">Inside each step, after extracting `idx.sprk_searchindexname`: if non-empty â†’ return that value. Otherwise, attempt a fallback read of `sprk_searchindexname` text column from the SAME entity (already available in the existing fetch via the entity's `attribute name='sprk_searchindexname'`); if non-empty â†’ log a structured WARNING `"PhaseG.TextFallback hit on {EntityType} {EntityId}"` and return the text value. Track these via App Insights.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `IAllowedIndexesProvider` interface in `Services/Ai/` with `Task&lt;bool&gt; IsAllowedAsync(string indexName, CancellationToken ct)`.</step>
    <step order="5">Implement `DataverseAllowedIndexesProvider` in `Services/Ai/`. Inject `IGenericEntityService` + `IMemoryCache` + `IOptions&lt;AiSearchOptions&gt;` + `ILogger&lt;DataverseAllowedIndexesProvider&gt;`. `IsAllowedAsync`: `_cache.GetOrCreate` keyed `sprk_aisearchindex:active`, TTL = 5 minutes. Load: FetchXml query `&lt;fetch&gt;&lt;entity name='sprk_aisearchindex'&gt;&lt;attribute name='sprk_searchindexname' /&gt;&lt;filter&gt;&lt;condition attribute='statecode' operator='eq' value='0' /&gt;&lt;/filter&gt;&lt;/entity&gt;&lt;/fetch&gt;`. Returns `HashSet&lt;string&gt;` of names. On exception OR empty result: log a single WARNING and return the static appsettings `AllowedIndexes` set (final fallback per Q4).</step>
    <step order="6">Register `DataverseAllowedIndexesProvider` as Singleton in `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`. Update `KnowledgeDeploymentService` to inject + use `IAllowedIndexesProvider` instead of reading `AiSearchOptions.AllowedIndexes` directly. ProblemDetails 400 `INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED` shape unchanged.</step>
    <step order="7">Run the existing BFF test suite (`dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`). All tests pass UNMODIFIED. If failures occur due to mock setup changes (the resolver now uses `RetrieveMultipleAsync` not `RetrieveAsync`), update the mocks minimally â€” but verify each test's INTENT is unchanged.</step>
    <step order="8">XML doc-comment all new interfaces/methods. Add Placement Justification block to `notes/phase-g/placement-justification.md`.</step>
    <step order="9">Run code-review + adr-check skills at Step 9.5 (FULL rigor). Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 102 ðŸ”² â†’ âœ….</step>
