  <notes>
    **Placement Justification** (binding per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`):
    The resolver and allow-list provider are tightly coupled to the existing `IKnowledgeDeploymentService` chain â€” both live in `Services/Ai/` per the in-BFF placement criterion. No facade needed (CRUD code does not consume AI internals; AI internals expose a richer source-of-truth). No new NuGet packages. New DI registrations: `IAllowedIndexesProvider` Singleton (`IMemoryCache` is already registered process-wide in `Program.cs`).

